TITLE: Arizona abortion protest: Police release tear gas, lawmakers ‘held hostage’ in Senate building
SUMMARY: The U.S. Supreme Court's overturning of Roe v. Wade has sparked a protest in Phoenix, Arizona, where protesters attempted to breach the state Senate building and created a dangerous situation for lawmakers.

TITLE: Pro-choice protesters burn American flag in streets of Washington DC after Roe v. Wade reversal
SUMMARY: Protesters in Washington D.C. burned the American flag following the Supreme Court's decision which overturned Roe v. Wade on Friday.

TITLE: Uvalde 1 month later: Father of daughter killed in mass shooting says family is strong, trying to get through
SUMMARY: One month has passed since a gunman shot and killed 19 children and two teachers at a school in Uvalde, Texas.

TITLE: Brian Laundrie's Gabby Petito confession: Experts weigh in on admitted killer's claims, 'This is all lies'
SUMMARY: Experts weigh in as the first public glimpse of a confession Brian Laundrie left in a notebook in the Florida swamp where he killed himself last year reveals his final words.

TITLE: One year after Surfside collapse, families of victims are still fighting for answers
SUMMARY: One year after a condominium building collapsed in Surfside, Florida, families of victims still don't have answers to how and why it happened. Ninety-eight people died in the collapse.

TITLE: Roe v. Wade overturned: Abortion clinics, churches, police brace for impact of Supreme Court ruling
SUMMARY: Abortion clinics, pregnancy centers, churches and police are ramping up security measures after the U.S. Supreme Court overturning Roe v. Wade on Friday.

TITLE: Oklahoma protesters, ACLU challenge anti-protest law
SUMMARY: Oklahoma citizens represented by the ACLU have filed a federal lawsuit which challenge the state's anti-protest law. They have also challenged their 2020 arrest.

TITLE: Iowa man who accidentally shot Marine with air rifle is fined
SUMMARY: An Iowa man seriously wounded a Marine after accidently shooting him with an air rifle while he was driving. The 71-year-old was fined $855 after pleading guilty to the misdemeanor.

TITLE: Washington DC bridge shut down after man scales archway to protest Roe v. Wade overturned
SUMMARY: A man scaled the Frederick Douglass Memorial Bridge in Washington, D.C. as a form of protest after the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade on Friday.

TITLE: Michigan Gov. Whitmer asks state's top court to rule on abortion rights
SUMMARY: The Michigan Supreme Court was urged by Gov. Gretchen Whitmer on Friday to rule on whether abortion is protected under the state's constitution.

TITLE: Texas lawmakers, leaders on both sides of the aisle react to landmark Supreme Court Roe ruling
SUMMARY: Texas is set to become the largest state in America to implement an abortion ban after the Supreme Court issued an opinion overturning Roe v. Wade on Friday.

TITLE: Gabby Petito murder: Brian Laundrie’s notebook confession revealed, 'I ended her life'
SUMMARY: Brian Laundrie and Gabby Petito set off on an ill-fated cross-country road trip one year ago this month. Brian Laundrie claimed responsibility for Petito's strangling death.

TITLE: Washington grain terminal will pay nearly $1 million to settle lawsuit
SUMMARY: A Washington grain terminal will pay nearly a million dollars to settle a lawsuit with the Columbia Riverkeeper, which claimed the terminal failed to get proper permits.

TITLE: Ohio man suspected of killing 2 found dead in Alabama
SUMMARY: An Ohio man who was suspected of killing a woman and a child was found dead in Alabama on Thursday. The man's wounds appeared to be self-inflicted.

TITLE: CA man accused of secretly recording 11-year-old girl as she changed
SUMMARY: A California man climbed onto the roof of a Massachusetts family's garage so he could record an 11-year-old girl as she changed in her bedroom, federal prosecutors say.

TITLE: NC felon sentenced to 10 years in prison after shooting at deputy
SUMMARY: A North Carolina man has been sentenced to 10 years in prison after being charged with being a felon in possession of a firearm. The man shot a rifle at a sheriff's deputy.

TITLE: SD expands policy for sale of alcohol at universities
SUMMARY: South Dakota will begin to sell more alcohol at school events for the following school year. The South Dakota Board of Regents approved an expanded alcohol sales policy.

TITLE: VT woman, dog attacked by coyote during walk
SUMMARY: A Vermont woman was attacked by a coyote whole walking her dog, receiving cuts to her face. Since 1991, there have been four recorded coyote attacks in Vermont since 1991.

TITLE: US heat causing roads to buckle, 'bleed'
SUMMARY: Extreme heat that has threatened U.S. states over the past couple of weeks is causing roads to buckle and "bleed." Drivers are being warned to take caution.

TITLE: Maine coast scattered with dead seagulls
SUMMARY: Dead seagulls are washing up on the Maine coast, following similar reports in Martha's Vineyard. Scientists fear these birds were the victims of the avian flu.
